## Test Smell Detection Report

**Project:** `DataAccess.IntegrationTests` · MSTest 4.1.0 · .NET 10  
**Scope:** Integration tests for `UserRepository` (SQLite in-memory)

---

### 1. Summary Dashboard

| Severity | Smell count | Affected tests |
|---|---:|---:|
| High | 3 | 3 |
| Medium | 0 | 0 |
| Low | 0 | 0 |
| **Total** | **3** | **3** |

---

### 2. Findings by Severity

#### ❶ Sleepy Test — High

**File:** `UserRepositoryIntegrationTests.cs` line 87  
**Method:** `NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay`

```csharp
Thread.Sleep(3000);
```

**Rationale:** A hard 3-second sleep adds flakiness (may be too short on slow CI, always wastes time otherwise) and makes the suite slow. The method is marked `async` but doesn't `await` anything.

**Fix:** Use a deterministic signal or poll with a short timeout:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public async Task NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay()
{
    var user = new User("dave@example.com", "Dave");
    _repository.Insert(user);

    var sent = await WaitUntilAsync(
        () => _repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id),
        timeout: TimeSpan.FromSeconds(5));

    Assert.IsTrue(sent, "Notification was not sent within timeout");
}
```

**Risk if unchanged:** Intermittent CI failures; 3 s of dead time per run.

---

#### ❷ Conditional Test Logic — High

**File:** `UserRepositoryIntegrationTests.cs` lines 101-108  
**Method:** `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType`

```csharp
if (loaded is PremiumUser premium)
{
    Assert.IsTrue(premium.DiscountRate > 0);
}
else
{
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded!.Name);
}
```

**Rationale:** The branch taken depends on runtime state. One path may never execute, silently hiding a bug. You cannot tell from a green result which assertion was verified.

**Fix:** Split into two deterministic tests with explicit setup:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_StandardUser_ReturnsName()
{
    var user = new User("eve@example.com", "Eve");
    _repository.Insert(user);

    var loaded = _repository.GetByEmail("eve@example.com");

    Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded.Name);
}

[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_PremiumUser_HasDiscountRate()
{
    var user = new PremiumUser("eve@example.com", "Eve", discountRate: 0.1m);
    _repository.Insert(user);

    var loaded = (PremiumUser)_repository.GetByEmail("eve@example.com")!;

    Assert.IsTrue(loaded.DiscountRate > 0);
}
```

**Risk if unchanged:** False confidence — a passing test may never exercise the intended assertion path.

---

#### ❸ Assertion-Free Test — High

**File:** `UserRepositoryIntegrationTests.cs` lines 113-119  
**Method:** `BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors`

```csharp
public void BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
    {
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));
    }
}
```

**Rationale:** This test only proves that no exception was thrown. Silent data corruption, duplicate entries, or partial inserts would all pass.

**Fix:** Assert the postcondition:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void BulkInsert_PersistsAllRecords()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
    {
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));
    }

    var users = _repository.ListAll();
    Assert.AreEqual(100, users.Count);
}
```

**Risk if unchanged:** False confidence — the test provides no evidence that data was actually persisted correctly.

---

### 3. Smell-Free Patterns (well done 👍)

The remaining 5 tests are clean and well-structured:

| Strength | Examples |
|---|---|
| Clear Arrange-Act-Assert | `InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase`, `DeleteUser_RemovesFromDatabase` |
| Descriptive naming (`Method_Scenario`) | All test names communicate intent |
| Proper test isolation | Per-test in-memory SQLite — no shared mutable state across tests |
| Lifecycle hooks | `TestInitialize` / `TestCleanup` correctly manage resources |
| Focused assertions | Each clean test verifies a single logical behavior |
| Legitimate integration patterns | `ConcurrentInserts_MaintainsIntegrity` correctly tests real concurrency |

---

### 4. Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Smell | Why first |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Assertion-Free (`BulkInsert`) | False confidence — hiding real bugs now |
| 2 | Conditional Test Logic (`GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType`) | False confidence — unknown which path runs |
| 3 | Sleepy Test (`NotifyOnInsert`) | Flakiness + slow feedback loop |

---

### Verdict

The suite is **mostly well-designed** — 5 of 8 tests follow clean integration-test patterns with good naming and isolation. The 3 smelly tests are concentrated and straightforward to fix. After addressing them your team will have a solid, trustworthy integration suite.
